originalText.text: The DEA wants to Ban "kratom" which is a safe, non addicting plant used for pain but at the same time talks about the overdoses & deaths of pharmaceutical drugs like fentanyl, oxycotin, etc.  There are no deaths from Kratom.  The only effect of taking too much kratom would be to vomit and no one wants that.  It's been used for years as an alternative to the harmful drugs made by "big pharma".  Where is the logic? Those who chose not to take drugs, who chose not to be addicted to harmful substances that can kill you have No alternative.  The DEA should ban the pharmaceutical companies instead of banning  natural God-given plants.  I guess this is what happens when there is No knowledge and too much power!
